      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Metronidazole, a common antibiotic for tooth infections, is a no-go for wine consumption. The combination of metronidazole and alcohol can lead to a nasty reaction, including a potentially life-threatening condition called methemoglobinemia. I wouldn't recommend having even one glass of wine with your dinner tonight, and definitely not until you've finished the full course of medication. Just stick to water and bland foods for the next week, and you'll be back to your normal self in no time.",
